Comment.val: /* Place holder for a new program to start the Spending Limit calculations with more compressed parameters The program is now empty. */

Text.val: When a reservation error has occurred or the authorisation failed--> remove the reservation.
Make sure the parameter p-o_Gefiatteerd is set to 0 when an error occured (Technical/Reservation/Functional)
First see if there are any Amounts To Authorize present:
There is no string with amounts to authorize, then calculate the SpendingLimit and return the values
There is a String with amounts present
The string is wrong
Set Gefiatteerd to 0, the amounts are supplied in a wrong format
Set the functional error code to 40
Create the FailureLogging to retain the information of the call
Apperently all amounts in the string have a value of 0,00. There is nothing to approve
Set Gefiatteerd to 1, there is no impact on the spending limit
When asked a reservation must be made:
There is an amount or are amounts present. Authorize this/these amount(s)
First calculate the amounts to authorize. These are calcuted per account currency
Then perform per account currency the authorisation
DbDel does not work for these DataSources, so delete tasks are used (they have not much data)
Watch Out!! Descending Sort on UAA_AMOUNT_ACC_CURRENCY to make sure that first the positive amounts (when present)
are processed and then the negative amounts
Per currency a reset of the amounts and worktables to prevent double data etc (not first time)
Perform the authorisation for the amount in account currency when the amount is negative
when the amount is positive or 0, then set v_UAA_APPROVED to 1 to accept the amount whitout checking
Set v_Gefiatteerd to 0 when authorisation was not possible, leave it at 0 eventhough the next amount could be authorised
Keep the last AuthorisationErrorCode (when there is one that's <> 0)
Keep the flag for TechnicalError (when ther is one)
Create Reservation when requested
When the amount is authorised and a reservation must be made, then:
1. Create the reservation (when not made already)
2. Add the initial amount(s) to the reservation
